result.execSummary:
The defendant Erik Daniel Tejada was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery with Use of Force [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $75.00 payable to Aaron R.--to be paid first. Restitution is joint and several with any co-actor ultimately convicted and sentenced in this matter. (cases 14CF293-14CF296). Restitution set at zero for all other victims.

Defendant to pay applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs. The Court ordered all financial obligations and restitution to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and as a condition of extended supervision. Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.
Consecutive to: Consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 151  days served

superMiscConds.notes: Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment.
Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms.

No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses).
No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.
No contact with victims Nicolas F., Aaron R., Alexandre J.-S., Elizabeth L., Karissa H., Mitchell H. and co-actors Mary Molale, Willmarvin Diaz-Boria, Jeriel Rodriguez, and Abigail Baez.

Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests.
Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent.
Participate in Anger Management.
Participate in Cognitive Thinking/Victim Program.
Provide DNA sample--pay surcharge.
Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.
Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment.

Defendant Erik Daniel Tejada in court with Attorney Enku E Lin.  Defendant Erik Daniel Tejada in custody.  Benjamin A Wesson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.
  
On motion of the State, Court ordered COUNT 1 AMENDED to: ROBBERY WITH USE OF FORCE, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.32(1)(a), a Class E Felony.  

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.

AS TO COUNTS 2 AND 3:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the state, the Court ordered Counts 2 and 3 DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing.

The Court ordered the Defendant REMANDED at this time.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 17, 2014 at 08:30 am.
